title.narrative: By 2021, Strategies to address crosscutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF mobilised expertise to support crosscutting issues in the areas of policy, planning, monitoring, advocacy, communication, Social and Behavioural Change (SBC), and provided guidance to government and partners throughout the year, to raise awareness and engagement in child rights with a wide range of stakeholders, including development partners, business, CSO and UN among others. Key achievements include the Country Programme Document (CPD) development and approval, technical support provision to the Government of Lao PDR in the finalisation 9th National Social and Economic Development Plan (NSEDP), and finalisation of the (C4D) Strategy.;;;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:01/02/2022
